name: UdaConnect
description: Refactoring UdaConnect application monolith architecture using a microservice architecture and implementing message passing strategies to improve its design.

name: mserv-rmq-app
description: This project aims at demonstrating how to use RabbitMQ and build a microservices application in dot.net core.

name: MicroBank
description: This repo contains sample ASP.NET Core application based on a Bank' money transfer logic. The primary goal of this sample is to demonstrate several software-architecture concepts like: Microservices, CQRS, Event Sourcing, Domain Driven Design (DDD), Eventual Consistency.

name: chatService-dotnetcore-signalR-mongodb
description: This is a simple chat service with dotnet core 3.1 web api and mongodb database with the use of signalR that can be used in any application with the need of chat functionality as a microservice.

name: ms-blizzard
description: A .NET Core microservice that gets information from Blizzard APIs. This is to be used by my front facing applications.

name: rhime
description: Rhime is a social media music recommendation application built using event-driven architectural patterns as a combination of multiple decoupled microservices with asynchronous communication between them.

name: ChatStockBot
description: This is a chat application written in C# .NET Core 2.0, using a ASP.NET Core Web Application implementing SignalR for realtime comunication and a Decoupled ChatBot Microservice that communicates with the WebApp using RabbitMQ.

name: Flask-JS-UI
description: Flask Standalone web application with builtin swagger UI and endpoint/revision performance monitoring

name: PhoneBookApp
description: The Phone Book Application is a simple phone book app written in C# .NET 6 for self-education on microservices architectures purposes. Heavily influenced on Microsoft's eShop example.

name: model_test_and_deploy
description: A web application built using ReactJS(frontend) and NodeJS(backend) for testing a machine learning model; either TF frozen_inference_graph.pb, TF saved_model, or Pytorch(experimental); and nuclio microservice function deployment as well.
